      "role": "user",
      "content": "thanks. but 3 to 30 hz is way too low for a human to hum, i can't even hit those notes. i need something more precise. if the storm is building up on the ionosphere, isn't there a higher resonant frequency i could use? like something in the kilohertz range that would actually interact with the atmospheric particles? can you give me a specific number i can aim for?",
